{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844073088,"sessionID":"ses_287725b68ffe31vjrcaNWO7QzD","part":{"id":"prt_d788e19f8001bZGm4VKmFUvMc5","messageID":"msg_d788df9bc0014YvW9GRmScDGMj","sessionID":"ses_287725b68ffe31vjrcaNWO7QzD","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-003 Design: CRD Shared Types and Constants (client-go)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-003  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** Small  \n9: \n10: Generate the Kubernetes client-go library for the API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`. The generated client provides programmatic access to `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs, including typed clients, informers, and listers.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Architecture\n15: \n16: ### High-Level Design\n17: \n18: The client-go library follows the standard Kubernetes code-generation pattern, providing a layered architecture for interacting with custom resources:\n19: \n20: ```\n21: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n22: │                           Consumer Applications                              │\n23: │  ┌───────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐ │\n24: │  │   Controllers │  │    CLI Tools  │  │  Workload Mgr │  │   Test Mocks │ │\n25: │  └───────┬───────┘  └───────┬───────┘  └───────┬───────┘  └──────┬───────┘ │\n26: └──────────┼──────────────────┼──────────────────┼─────────────────┼─────────┘\n27:            │                  │                  │                 │\n28:            ▼                  ▼                  ▼                 ▼\n29: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n30: │                           client-go Library                                  │\n31: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n32: │  │                        Clientset (Interface)                          │   │\n33: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │   │\n34: │  │  │                    RuntimeV1alpha1Interface                     │  │   │\n35: │  │  │  ┌─────────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐  │  │   │\n36: │  │  │  │ AgentRuntimeInterface│  │    CodeInterpreterInterface     │  │  │   │\n37: │  │  │  │ · Create()          │  │  · Create()                     │  │  │   │\n38: │  │  │  │ · Get()             │  │  · Get()                        │  │  │   │\n39: │  │  │  │ · List()            │  │  · List()                       │  │  │   │\n40: │  │  │  │ · Watch()           │  │  · Watch()                      │  │  │   │\n41: │  │  │  │ · Update()          │  │  · Update()                     │  │  │   │\n42: │  │  │  │ · UpdateStatus()    │  │  · UpdateStatus()               │  │  │   │\n43: │  │  │  │ · Delete()          │  │  · Delete()                     │  │  │   │\n44: │  │  │  │ · Patch()           │  │  · Patch()                      │  │  │   │\n45: │  │  │  └─────────────────────┘  └─────────────────────────────────┘  │  │   │\n46: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │   │\n47: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n48: │                                                                              │\n49: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n50: │  │                     SharedInformerFactory                             │   │\n51: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │   │\n52: │  │  │  ┌─────────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐  │  │   │\n53: │  │  │  │ AgentRuntimeInformer│  │    CodeInterpreterInformer      │  │  │   │\n54: │  │  │  │ · Informer()        │  │  · Informer()                   │  │  │   │\n55: │  │  │  │ · Lister()          │  │  · Lister()                     │  │  │   │\n56: │  │  │  └─────────────────────┘  └─────────────────────────────────┘  │  │   │\n57: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │   │\n58: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n59: │                                                                              │\n60: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n61: │  │                      Lister Interfaces                                │   │\n62: │  │  ┌─────────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐        │   │\n63: │  │  │ AgentRuntimeLister  │  │    CodeInterpreterLister        │        │   │\n64: │  │  │ · List()            │  │  · List()                       │        │   │\n65: │  │  │ · AgentRuntimes()   │  │  · CodeInterpreters()           │        │   │\n66: │  │  │   (namespace lister)│  │    (namespace lister)           │        │   │\n67: │  │  └─────────────────────┘  └─────────────────────────────────┘        │   │\n68: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n69: │                                                                              │\n70: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n71: │  │                    Scheme / Codecs (register.go)                      │   │\n72: │  │  · AddToScheme()  · Scheme  · Codecs  · ParameterCodec               │   │\n73: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n74: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n75: ```\n76: \n77: ### Component Interactions\n78: \n79: | Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n80: |-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n81: | **Clientset** | Entry point for all API operations | `*rest.Config` | Typed clients per group-version |\n82: | **Typed Client** | CRUD operations for specific resource | Context, resource object | Result object, error |\n83: | **Informer** | Watch and cache resources | Client, resync period | `cache.SharedIndexInformer` |\n84: | **Lister** | Read-only cached access | Label selectors | Cached resource list |\n85: | **Scheme** | Type registration and serialization | Raw bytes/Objects | Typed objects |\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: ## Data Structures\n90: \n91: ### Clientset\n92: \n93: #### Interface Definition\n94: \n95: ```go\n96: // Interface provides access to the AgentCube API clientset.\n97: type Interface interface {\n98:     Discovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n99:     RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n100: }\n101: ```\n102: \n103: #### Clientset Struct\n104: \n105: ```go\n106: // Clientset contains the clients for groups. Each group has exactly one\n107: // version included in a Clientset.\n108: type Clientset struct {\n109:     *discovery.DiscoveryClient\n110:     runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client\n111: }\n112: ```\n113: \n114: #### Constructors\n115: \n116: | Function | Signature | Description |\n117: |----------|-----------|-------------|\n118: | `NewForConfig` | `func(c *rest.Config) (*Clientset, error)` | Creates clientset from REST config |\n119: | `NewForConfigAndClient` | `func(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*Clientset, error)` | Creates with custom HTTP client |\n120: | `NewForConfigOrDie` | `func(c *rest.Config) *Clientset` | Creates or panics on error |\n121: | `New` | `func(c rest.Interface) *Clientset` | Creates from REST interface |\n122: \n123: ### Typed Client — `runtime/v1alpha1`\n124: \n125: #### RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n126: \n127: ```go\n128: // RuntimeV1alpha1Interface provides access to runtime/v1alpha1 resources.\n129: type RuntimeV1alpha1Interface interface {\n130:     RESTClient() rest.Interface\n131:     AgentRuntimesGetter\n132:     CodeInterpretersGetter\n133: }\n134: ```\n135: \n136: #### AgentRuntimesGetter / AgentRuntimeInterface\n137: \n138: ```go\n139: // AgentRuntimesGetter provides access to AgentRuntime resources.\n140: type AgentRuntimesGetter interface {\n141:     AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface\n142: }\n143: \n144: // AgentRuntimeInterface provides CRUD operations for AgentRuntime resources.\n145: type AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n146:     Create(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n147:     Update(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n148:     UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n149:     Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n150:     DeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n151:     Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n152:     List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n153:     Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n154:     Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n155:     AgentRuntimeExpansion\n156: }\n157: ```\n158: \n159: **REST Resource:** `agentruntimes` (plural)\n160: \n161: #### CodeInterpretersGetter / CodeInterpreterInterface\n162: \n163: ```go\n164: // CodeInterpretersGetter provides access to CodeInterpreter resources.\n165: type CodeInterpretersGetter interface {\n166:     CodeInterpreters(namespace string) CodeInterpreterInterface\n167: }\n168: \n169: // CodeInterpreterInterface provides CRUD operations for CodeInterpreter resources.\n170: type CodeInterpreterInterface interface {\n171:     Create(ctx context.Context, codeInterpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n172:     Update(ctx context.Context, codeInterpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n173:     UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, codeInterpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n174:     Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n175:     DeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n176:     Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n177:     List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterList, error)\n178:     Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n179:     Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n180:     CodeInterpreterExpansion\n181: }\n182: ```\n183: \n184: **REST Resource:** `codeinterpreters` (plural)\n185: \n186: #### Expansion Hooks\n187: \n188: ```go\n189: // AgentRuntimeExpansion allows adding custom methods to AgentRuntimeInterface.\n190: type AgentRuntimeExpansion interface{}\n191: \n192: // CodeInterpreterExpansion allows adding custom methods to CodeInterpreterInterface.\n193: type CodeInterpreterExpansion interface{}\n194: ```\n195: \n196: ### Scheme\n197: \n198: #### Package: `clientset/versioned/scheme/`\n199: \n200: ```go\n201: // Package scheme contains the scheme registration for the runtime/v1alpha1 API group.\n202: \n203: var (\n204:     // Scheme is the runtime.Scheme to which types are registered.\n205:     Scheme = runtime.NewScheme()\n206: \n207:     // Codecs provides access to the encoder and decoder for this scheme.\n208:     Codecs = serializer.NewCodecFactory(Scheme)\n209: \n210:     // ParameterCodec handles parameter encoding/decoding.\n211:     ParameterCodec = runtime.NewParameterCodec(Scheme)\n212: )\n213: \n214: // AddToScheme adds runtime/v1alpha1 types to the given scheme.\n215: func AddToScheme(scheme *runtime.Scheme) error\n216: ```\n217: \n218: ### Informer Factory\n219: \n220: #### SharedInformerFactory Interface\n221: \n222: ```go\n223: // SharedInformerFactory provides access to shared informers for resources.\n224: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n225:     internalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory\n226:     Start(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n227:     Shutdown()\n228:     WaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) map[reflect.Type]bool\n229:     ForResource(resource schema.GroupVersionResource) (GenericInformer, error)\n230:     InformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n231:     Runtime() externalversionsruntime.Interface\n232: }\n233: ```\n234: \n235: #### Factory Options\n236: \n237: ```go\n238: // SharedInformerOption configures the SharedInformerFactory.\n239: type SharedInformerOption func(*sharedInformerFactory)\n240: \n241: // Available options:\n242: func WithCustomResyncConfig(config map[v1.Object]time.Duration) SharedInformerOption\n243: func WithTweakListOptions(tweakListOptions internalinterfaces.TweakListOptionsFunc) SharedInformerOption\n244: func WithNamespace(namespace string) SharedInformerOption\n245: func WithTransform(transform cache.TransformFunc) SharedInformerOption\n246: ```\n247: \n248: #### Factory Constructors\n249: \n250: | Function | Signature |\n251: |----------|-----------|\n252: | `NewSharedInformerFactory` | `func(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration) SharedInformerFactory` |\n253: | `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions` | `func(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration, options ...SharedInformerOption) SharedInformerFactory` |\n254: \n255: ### Per-Type Informers\n256: \n257: #### AgentRuntimeInformer\n258: \n259: ```go\n260: // AgentRuntimeInformer provides access to AgentRuntime informers.\n261: type AgentRuntimeInformer interface {\n262:     Informer() cache.SharedIndexInformer\n263:     Lister() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n264: }\n265: \n266: // Constructor functions:\n267: func NewAgentRuntimeInformer(client versioned.Interface, namespace string, resyncPeriod time.Duration, indexers cache.Indexers) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n268: func NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer(client versioned.Interface, namespace string, resyncPeriod time.Duration, indexers cache.Indexers, tweakListOptions internalinterfaces.TweakListOptionsFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n269: ```\n270: \n271: #### CodeInterpreterInformer\n272: \n273: ```go\n274: // CodeInterpreterInformer provides access to CodeInterpreter informers.\n275: type CodeInterpreterInformer interface {\n276:     Informer() cache.SharedIndexInformer\n277:     Lister() runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister\n278: }\n279: \n280: // Constructor functions:\n281: func NewCodeInterpreterInformer(client versioned.Interface, namespace string, resyncPeriod time.Duration, indexers cache.Indexers) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n282: func NewFilteredCodeInterpreterInformer(client versioned.Interface, namespace string, resyncPeriod time.Duration, indexers cache.Indexers, tweakListOptions internalinterfaces.TweakListOptionsFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n283: ```\n284: \n285: ### Listers\n286: \n287: #### AgentRuntimeLister\n288: \n289: ```go\n290: // AgentRuntimeLister provides read-only access to AgentRuntime list.\n291: type AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n292:     List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n293:     AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n294:     AgentRuntimeListerExpansion\n295: }\n296: \n297: // AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister provides namespaced listing.\n298: type AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n299:     List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n300:     Get(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n301:     AgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion\n302: }\n303: ```\n304: \n305: #### CodeInterpreterLister\n306: \n307: ```go\n308: // CodeInterpreterLister provides read-only access to CodeInterpreter list.\n309: type CodeInterpreterLister interface {\n310:     List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n311:     CodeInterpreters(namespace string) CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister\n312:     CodeInterpreterListerExpansion\n313: }\n314: \n315: // CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister provides namespaced listing.\n316: type CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister interface {\n317:     List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n318:     Get(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n319:     CodeInterpreterNamespaceListerExpansion\n320: }\n321: ```\n322: \n323: ### Fake Clientset (for Testing)\n324: \n325: ```go\n326: // Package fake provides a fake clientset for testing.\n327: \n328: // NewSimpleClientset returns a clientset that will respond with the provided objects.\n329: func NewSimpleClientset(objs ...runtime.Object) *Clientset\n330: \n331: // NewClientset returns a clientset that uses the provided scheme.\n332: func NewClientset(scheme *runtime.Scheme, tracker testing.ObjectTracker) *Clientset\n333: ```\n334: \n335: ---\n336: \n337: ## API Contracts\n338: \n339: ### REST Resource Mappings\n340: \n341: | Resource | API Group | Version | Kind | Plural | Short Names |\n342: |----------|-----------|---------|------|--------|-------------|\n343: | AgentRuntime | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` | `AgentRuntime` | `agentruntimes` | `ar`, `ars` |\n344: | CodeInterpreter | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` | `CodeInterpreter` | `codeinterpreters` | `ci`, `cis` |\n345: \n346: ### HTTP Endpoints\n347: \n348: #### AgentRuntime Endpoints\n349: \n350: | Method | Path | Description |\n351: |--------|------|-------------|\n352: | GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes` | List |\n353: | POST | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes` | Create |\n354: | GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Get |\n355: | PUT | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Update |\n356: | PATCH | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Patch |\n357: | DELETE | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Delete |\n358: | GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}/status` | Get Status |\n359: | PUT | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}/status` | Update Status |\n360: \n361: #### CodeInterpreter Endpoints\n362: \n363: | Method | Path | Description |\n364: |--------|------|-------------|\n365: | GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | List |\n366: | POST | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | Create |\n367: | GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Get |\n368: | PUT | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Update |\n369: | PATCH | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Patch |\n370: | DELETE | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Delete |\n371: | GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status` | Get Status |\n372: | PUT | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status` | Update Status |\n373: \n374: ### Generic Resource Routing\n375: \n376: ```go\n377: // ForResource returns a GenericInformer for the specified resource.\n378: func (f *sharedInformerFactory) ForResource(resource schema.GroupVersionResource) (GenericInformer, error) {\n379:     switch resource {\n380:     case v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"agentruntimes\"):\n381:         return &genericInformer{resource: resource.GroupResource(), informer: f.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()}, nil\n382:     case v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"codeinterpreters\"):\n383:         return &genericInformer{resource: resource.GroupResource(), informer: f.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Informer()}, nil\n384:     default:\n385:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"no informer found for %v\", resource)\n386:     }\n387: }\n388: ```\n389: \n390: ---\n391: \n392: ## Error Handling\n393: \n394: ### Error Categories\n395: \n396: | Category | Source | Handling Strategy |\n397: |----------|--------|-------------------|\n398: | **Connection Errors** | REST client, network layer | Retry with exponential backoff |\n399: | **API Errors** | Kubernetes API server | Check error type with `apierrors` helpers |\n400: | **Validation Errors** | API server validation | Return 422, examine error details |\n401: | **Not Found** | Resource doesn't exist | Check `apierrors.IsNotFound(err)` |\n402: | **Conflict** | Resource version mismatch | Retry after re-fetching resource |\n403: | **Forbidden** | RBAC denied | Log and alert, escalate permissions |\n404: \n405: ### Error Handling Patterns\n406: \n407: #### Typed Client Error Handling\n408: \n409: ```go\n410: // Example: Handling errors from AgentRuntime client\n411: func (c *Controller) reconcileAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, name, namespace string) error {\n412:     ar, err := c.client.AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n413:     if err != nil {\n414:         if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n415:             // Resource was deleted - clean up\n416:             return c.handleDeleted(name)\n417:         }\n418:         if apierrors.IsTimeout(err) {\n419:             // Temporary error - retry later\n420:             return fmt.Errorf(\"timeout fetching AgentRuntime: %w\", err)\n421:         }\n422:         // Other errors - wrap and return\n423:         return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get AgentRuntime: %w\", err)\n424:     }\n425: \n426:     // Process the resource\n427:     return c.processAgentRuntime(ar)\n428: }\n429: ```\n430: \n431: #### Informer Error Handling\n432: \n433: ```go\n434: // Example: Setting up error handlers for informers\n435: func (c *Controller) setupInformers() {\n436:     agentRuntimeInformer := c.informerFactory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()\n437:     \n438:     // Add event handlers\n439:     agentRuntimeInformer.AddEventHandler(cache.ResourceEventHandlerFuncs{\n440:         AddFunc: c.onAgentRuntimeAdd,\n441:         UpdateFunc: c.onAgentRuntimeUpdate,\n442:         DeleteFunc: c.onAgentRuntimeDelete,\n443:     })\n444: \n445:     // Handle informer errors\n446:     agentRuntimeInformer.SetWatchErrorHandler(func(r *cache.Reflector, err error) {\n447:         klog.Errorf(\"AgentRuntime watch error: %v\", err)\n448:         // Metrics and alerting\n449:         metrics.RecordWatchError(\"agentruntime\", err)\n450:     })\n451: }\n452: ```\n453: \n454: #### Lister Error Handling\n455: \n456: ```go\n457: // Example: Handling lister errors (should be rare, usually cache is synced)\n458: func (c *Controller) listAgentRuntimes(selector labels.Selector) ([]*v1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error) {\n459:     runtimes, err := c.agentRuntimeLister.List(selector)\n460:     if err != nil {\n461:         // This is typically a programming error or cache not synced\n462:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to list AgentRuntimes from cache: %w\", err)\n463:     }\n464:     return runtimes, nil\n465: }\n466: ```\n467: \n468: ### Error Propagation Best Practices\n469: \n470: 1. **Always wrap errors** with context using `fmt.Errorf(\"...: %w\", err)`\n471: 2. **Check specific error types** using `apierrors` helpers before wrapping\n472: 3. **Log at appropriate levels** - debug for retryable, error for permanent\n473: 4. **Use structured logging** with resource identifiers\n474: 5. **Return early** on unrecoverable errors\n475: \n476: ---\n477: \n478: ## Testing Strategy\n479: \n480: ### Unit Tests\n481: \n482: #### Fake Clientset Tests\n483: \n484: ```go\n485: // Test using fake clientset for AgentRuntime operations\n486: func TestAgentRuntimeCreate(t *testing.T) {\n487:     // Create fake clientset\n488:     client := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n489: \n490:     // Create a test AgentRuntime\n491:     ar := &v1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n492:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n493:             Name:      \"test-ar\",\n494:             Namespace: \"default\",\n495:         },\n496:         Spec: v1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n497:             Image: \"agent:latest\",\n498:         },\n499:     }\n500: \n501:     // Create the resource\n502:     created, err := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Create(context.Background(), ar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n503:     require.NoError(t, err)\n504:     assert.Equal(t, \"test-ar\", created.Name)\n505:     assert.Equal(t, \"agent:latest\", created.Spec.Image)\n506: \n507:     // Verify it exists\n508:     fetched, err := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Get(context.Background(), \"test-ar\", metav1.GetOptions{})\n509:     require.NoError(t, err)\n510:     assert.Equal(t, created.UID, fetched.UID)\n511: }\n512: ```\n513: \n514: #### Fake Lister Tests\n515: \n516: ```go\n517: // Test using fake listers\n518: func TestAgentRuntimeLister(t *testing.T) {\n519:     // Create fake objects\n520:     ar1 := &v1alpha1.AgentRuntime{ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{Name: \"ar1\", Namespace: \"ns1\"}}\n521:     ar2 := &v1alpha1.AgentRuntime{ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{Name: \"ar2\", Namespace: \"ns1\"}}\n522:     ar3 := &v1alpha1.AgentRuntime{ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{Name: \"ar3\", Namespace: \"ns2\"}}\n523: \n524:     // Create indexer\n525:     indexer := cache.NewIndexer(cache.MetaNamespaceKeyFunc, cache.Indexers{cache.NamespaceIndex: cache.MetaNamespaceIndexFunc})\n526:     indexer.Add(ar1)\n527:     indexer.Add(ar2)\n528:     indexer.Add(ar3)\n529: \n530:     // Create lister\n531:     lister := runtimev1alpha1.NewAgentRuntimeLister(indexer)\n532: \n533:     // Test List all\n534:     all, err := lister.List(labels.Everything())\n535:     require.NoError(t, err)\n536:     assert.Len(t, all, 3)\n537: \n538:     // Test List by namespace\n539:     ns1Runtimes, err := lister.AgentRuntimes(\"ns1\").List(labels.Everything())\n540:     require.NoError(t, err)\n541:     assert.Len(t, ns1Runtimes, 2)\n542: \n543:     // Test Get\n544:     ar, err := lister.AgentRuntimes(\"ns1\").Get(\"ar1\")\n545:     require.NoError(t, err)\n546:     assert.Equal(t, \"ar1\", ar.Name)\n547: }\n548: ```\n549: \n550: ### Integration Tests\n551: \n552: ```go\n553: // Integration test using real API server (envtest)\n554: func TestAgentRuntimeLifecycle(t *testing.T) {\n555:     // Setup envtest\n556:     testEnv := &envtest.Environment{\n557:         CRDDirectoryPaths: []string{\"../../config/crd/bases\"},\n558:     }\n559:     cfg, err := testEnv.Start()\n560:     require.NoError(t, err)\n561:     defer testEnv.Stop()\n562: \n563:     // Create clientset\n564:     client, err := clientset.NewForConfig(cfg)\n565:     require.NoError(t, err)\n566: \n567:     ctx := context.Background()\n568: \n569:     // Create namespace\n570:     k8sClient, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(cfg)\n571:     require.NoError(t, err)\n572:     _, err = k8sClient.CoreV1().Namespaces().Create(ctx, &corev1.Namespace{\n573:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{Name: \"test-ns\"},\n574:     }, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n575:     require.NoError(t, err)\n576: \n577:     // Create AgentRuntime\n578:     ar := &v1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n579:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n580:             Name:      \"test-ar\",\n581:             Namespace: \"test-ns\",\n582:         },\n583:         Spec: v1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n584:             Image: \"test-image:latest\",\n585:         },\n586:     }\n587:     created, err := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").Create(ctx, ar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n588:     require.NoError(t, err)\n589: \n590:     // Update status\n591:     created.Status.Phase = v1alpha1.AgentRuntimePhaseRunning\n592:     updated, err := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").UpdateStatus(ctx, created, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n593:     require.NoError(t, err)\n594:     assert.Equal(t, v1alpha1.AgentRuntimePhaseRunning, updated.Status.Phase)\n595: \n596:     // Delete\n597:     err = client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").Delete(ctx, \"test-ar\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})\n598:     require.NoError(t, err)\n599: \n600:     // Verify deletion\n601:     _, err = client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").Get(ctx, \"test-ar\", metav1.GetOptions{})\n602:     assert.True(t, apierrors.IsNotFound(err))\n603: }\n604: ```\n605: \n606: ### Code Generation Verification\n607: \n608: ```bash\n609: #!/bin/bash\n610: # verify-codegen.sh\n611: \n612: set -e\n613: \n614: echo \"=== Verifying client-go code generation ===\"\n615: \n616: # Generate code\n617: echo \"Running code generation...\"\n618: make gen-client\n619: \n620: # Build to verify compilation\n621: echo \"Building generated code...\"\n622: go build ./client-go/...\n623: \n624: # Run tests\n625: echo \"Running client-go tests...\"\n626: go test ./client-go/...\n627: \n628: # Check for uncommitted changes\n629: if [[ -n $(git status --porcelain client-go/) ]]; then\n630:     echo \"ERROR: Generated code is out of date. Run 'make gen-client' and commit changes.\"\n631:     git diff client-go/\n632:     exit 1\n633: fi\n634: \n635: echo \"=== Verification passed ===\"\n636: ```\n637: \n638: ### Test Coverage Requirements\n639: \n640: | Component | Coverage Target | Testing Method |\n641: |-----------|-----------------|----------------|\n642: | Clientset Interface | 90%+ | Unit tests with fakes |\n643: | Typed Clients | 85%+ | Unit tests with fakes |\n644: | Scheme Registration | 100% | Integration tests |\n645: | Informers | 80%+ | Integration tests |\n646: | Listers | 100% | Unit tests with fake indexers |\n647: | Fake Clientset | 100% | Self-testing via usage |\n648: \n649: ### Continuous Integration\n650: \n651: ```yaml\n652: # .github/workflows/client-go.yaml\n653: name: client-go\n654: \n655: on:\n656:   push:\n657:     paths:\n658:       - 'pkg/apis/**'\n659:       - 'client-go/**'\n660:       - 'hack/**'\n661:   pull_request:\n662:     paths:\n663:       - 'pkg/apis/**'\n664:       - 'client-go/**'\n665:       - 'hack/**'\n666: \n667: jobs:\n668:   verify:\n669:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n670:     steps:\n671:       - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n672: \n673:       - name: Set up Go\n674:         uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n675:         with:\n676:           go-version: '1.23'\n677: \n678:       - name: Verify code generation\n679:         run: make verify-codegen\n680: \n681:       - name: Build client-go\n682:         run: go build ./client-go/...\n683: \n684:       - name: Test client-go\n685:         run: go test -v -race ./client-go/...\n686: \n687:       - name: Test with real types\n688:         run: go test -v ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n689: ```\n690: \n691: ---\n692: \n693: ## File Layout\n694: \n695: ```\n696: client-go/\n697: ├── clientset/\n698: │   └── versioned/\n699: │       ├── clientset.go                    # Clientset struct and Interface\n700: │       ├── scheme/\n701: │       │   ├── doc.go                      # Package documentation\n702: │       │   └── register.go                 # Scheme registration\n703: │       ├── typed/\n704: │       │   └── runtime/\n705: │       │       └── v1alpha1/\n706: │       │           ├── doc.go              # Package documentation\n707: │       │           ├── runtime_client.go   # RuntimeV1alpha1Client\n708: │       │           ├── agentruntime.go     # AgentRuntimeInterface\n709: │       │           ├── codeinterpreter.go  # CodeInterpreterInterface\n710: │       │           ├── generated_expansion.go  # Expansion interfaces\n711: │       │           └── fake/\n712: │       │               ├── doc.go\n713: │       │               ├── fake_runtime_client.go\n714: │       │               ├── fake_agentruntime.go\n715: │       │               └── fake_codeinterpreter.go\n716: │       └── fake/\n717: │           ├── doc.go\n718: │           ├── clientset_generated.go      # Fake Clientset\n719: │           └── register.go\n720: ├── informers/\n721: │   └── externalversions/\n722: │       ├── factory.go                      # SharedInformerFactory\n723: │       ├── generic.go                      # Generic informer routing\n724: │       ├── internalinterfaces/\n725: │       │   └── factory_interfaces.go       # Internal interfaces\n726: │       └── runtime/\n727: │           ├── interface.go                # Group interface\n728: │           └── v1alpha1/\n729: │               ├── interface.go            # Version interface\n730: │               ├── agentruntime.go         # AgentRuntimeInformer\n731: │               └── codeinterpreter.go      # CodeInterpreterInformer\n732: └── listers/\n733:     └── runtime/\n734:         └── v1alpha1/\n735:             ├── agentruntime.go             # AgentRuntimeLister\n736:             ├── codeinterpreter.go          # CodeInterpreterLister\n737:             └── expansion_generated.go      # Lister expansion interfaces\n738: ```\n739: \n740: ---\n741: \n742: ## Code Generation\n743: \n744: ### Generation Tool: k8s.io/code-generator\n745: \n746: ```bash\n747: # Makefile target for client generation\n748: gen-client:\n749:     ./hack/update-codegen.sh\n750: \n751: # Verification target\n752: verify-codegen:\n753:     ./hack/verify-codegen.sh\n754: ```\n755: \n756: ### Generation Script\n757: \n758: ```bash\n759: #!/bin/bash\n760: # hack/update-codegen.sh\n761: \n762: set -euo pipefail\n763: \n764: SCRIPT_ROOT=$(dirname \"${BASH_SOURCE[0]}\")/..\n765: CODEGEN_PKG=${CODEGEN_PKG:-$(cd \"${SCRIPT_ROOT}\"; go list -m -f '{{.Dir}}' k8s.io/code-generator)}\n766: \n767: # Generate clientset, informers, listers\n768: \"${CODEGEN_PKG}/generate-groups.sh\" \\\n769:     \"client,informer,lister\" \\\n770:     github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go \\\n771:     github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis \\\n772:     \"runtime:v1alpha1\" \\\n773:     --go-header-file \"${SCRIPT_ROOT}/hack/boilerplate.go.txt\" \\\n774:     --output-base \"${SCRIPT_ROOT}\" \\\n775:     --with-watch\n776: ```\n777: \n778: ### Generation Parameters\n779: \n780: | Parameter | Value | Description |\n781: |-----------|-------|-------------|\n782: | Generators | `client,informer,lister` | What to generate |\n783: | Output Package | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Go import path |\n784: | API Package | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis` | Source types location |\n785: | Groups | `runtime:v1alpha1` | Group:version pairs |\n786: | Flags | `--with-watch` | Enable Watch support |\n787: \n788: ---\n789: \n790: ## Dependencies\n791: \n792: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n793: |------------|---------|---------|\n794: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | TypeMeta, ObjectMeta, runtime.Object |\n795: | `k8s.io/client-go` | `v0.34.1` | REST client, informers, listers |\n796: | `k8s.io/code-generator` | `v0.34.1` | Code generation tools |\n797: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis` | Local | Source API types |\n798: \n799: ---\n800: \n801: ## Design Decisions\n802: \n803: ### 1. Separate client-go Module\n804: \n805: **Decision**: Place generated code in `client-go/` directory with its own go.mod (optional).\n806: \n807: **Rationale**:\n808: - Consumers can depend only on the client without pulling in controller dependencies\n809: - Aligns with Kubernetes ecosystem conventions (e.g., `k8s.io/client-go`)\n810: - Cleaner dependency graph for external tools\n811: \n812: ### 2. Standard Code Generator\n813: \n814: **Decision**: Use `k8s.io/code-generator` instead of custom tooling.\n815: \n816: **Rationale**:\n817: - Industry standard for Kubernetes CRD clients\n818: - Automatic updates with Kubernetes version bumps\n819: - Well-tested and maintained by the community\n820: - Supports all required features (watch, informers, listers)\n821: \n822: ### 3. Expansion Interfaces\n823: \n824: **Decision**: Generate empty expansion interfaces for all typed clients and listers.\n825: \n826: **Rationale**:\n827: - Allows extending generated interfaces without modifying generated code\n828: - Follows Kubernetes client-go pattern\n829: - Enables custom helper methods while maintaining interface compatibility\n830: \n831: ### 4. Fake Clientset\n832: \n833: **Decision**: Include complete fake implementation for all interfaces.\n834: \n835: **Rationale**:\n836: - Essential for unit testing controllers\n837: - Provides in-memory object tracking\n838: - Supports all CRUD operations including Watch\n839: - No external dependencies required for testing\n840: \n841: ---\n842: \n843: ## References\n844: \n845: - [Kubernetes client-go](https://github.com/kubernetes/client-go)\n846: - [code-generator](https://github.com/kubernetes/code-generator)\n847: - [sample-controller](https://github.com/kubernetes/sample-controller) - Example usage pattern\n848: - [Kubernetes Custom Resources](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/)\n849: \n850: ---\n851: \n852: ## Change Log\n853: \n854: | Version | Date | Changes |\n855: |---------|------|---------|\n856: | 1.0 | 2026-04-11 | Initial design for AR-003 client-go library |\n\n(End of file - total 856 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-003 Design: CRD Shared Types and Constants (client-go)\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-003  \n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** Small  \n\nGenerate the Kubernetes client-go library for the API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`. The generated client provides programmatic access to `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs, including typed clients, informers, and listers.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\nThe client-go library follows the standard Kubernetes code-generation pattern, providing a layered architecture for interacting with custom resources:\n\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775844073074,"end":1775844073085}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844073092,"sessionID":"ses_287725b68ffe31vjrcaNWO7QzD","part":{"id":"prt_d788e1162001azQON3yeakCbpN","messageID":"msg_d788df9bc0014YvW9GRmScDGMj","sessionID":"ses_287725b68ffe31vjrcaNWO7QzD","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-003 — CRD Shared Types and Constants\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-003  \n6: **Module:** pkg/apis  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** S  \n9: \n10: Extract shared types and constants from AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRD definitions to reduce code duplication and establish a common type foundation for the runtime API group.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Shared Phase Type Definition\n17: \n18: The system SHALL define a common `SandboxPhase` type to represent the lifecycle phase of sandbox-based resources, replacing the individual phase types in AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: SandboxPhase type is defined\n21: - **GIVEN** the shared types file in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n22: - **WHEN** inspecting the type definitions\n23: - **THEN** it SHALL contain a `SandboxPhase` string type with kubebuilder validation enum: `Pending`, `Running`, `Succeeded`, `Failed`, `Unknown`\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: SandboxPhase constants are defined\n26: - **GIVEN** the shared types file\n27: - **WHEN** inspecting the constants\n28: - **THEN** it SHALL define the following constants:\n29:   - `SandboxPhasePending`\n30:   - `SandboxPhaseRunning`\n31:   - `SandboxPhaseSucceeded`\n32:   - `SandboxPhaseFailed`\n33:   - `SandboxPhaseUnknown`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime uses SandboxPhase\n36: - **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeStatus` struct in `agentruntime_types.go`\n37: - **WHEN** inspecting the `Phase` field\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL use `SandboxPhase` instead of `AgentRuntimePhase`\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: SandboxPhase values match legacy AgentRuntimePhase\n41: - **GIVEN** the `SandboxPhase` type and constants\n42: - **WHEN** comparing to legacy `AgentRuntimePhase` values\n43: - **THEN** the string values SHALL match exactly (e.g., `SandboxPhasePending` = \"Pending\")\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ### Requirement: Shared Condition Type Definition\n48: \n49: The system SHALL define a common `SandboxConditionType` type for conditions that apply to both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: SandboxConditionType type is defined\n52: - **GIVEN** the shared types file\n53: - **WHEN** inspecting the type definitions\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL contain a `SandboxConditionType` string type with kubebuilder validation enum\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: SandboxConditionType constants are defined\n57: - **GIVEN** the shared types file\n58: - **WHEN** inspecting the constants\n59: - **THEN** it SHALL define the following constants:\n60:   - `SandboxConditionReady` — indicates the resource is ready to accept requests\n61:   - `SandboxConditionSandboxCreated` — indicates the sandbox has been created\n62:   - `SandboxConditionSandboxReady` — indicates the sandbox is ready for use\n63:   - `SandboxConditionFailed` — indicates the resource has failed\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime uses SandboxConditionType\n66: - **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeCondition` struct in `agentruntime_types.go`\n67: - **WHEN** inspecting the `Type` field\n68: - **THEN** it SHALL use `SandboxConditionType` instead of `AgentRuntimeConditionType`\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter uses SandboxConditionType\n71: - **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterCondition` struct in `codeinterpreter_types.go`\n72: - **WHEN** inspecting the `Type` field\n73: - **THEN** it SHALL use `SandboxConditionType` instead of `CodeInterpreterConditionType`\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Shared Condition Struct Definition\n78: \n79: The system SHALL define a common `SandboxCondition` struct to represent conditions for sandbox-based resources.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: SandboxCondition struct is defined\n82: - **GIVEN** the shared types file\n83: - **WHEN** inspecting the struct definitions\n84: - **THEN** it SHALL contain a `SandboxCondition` struct with the following fields:\n85:   - `Type` (`SandboxConditionType`, required)\n86:   - `Status` (`corev1.ConditionStatus`, required, enum: True, False, Unknown)\n87:   - `LastTransitionTime` (`metav1.Time`, optional)\n88:   - `Reason` (string, optional)\n89:   - `Message` (string, optional)\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime uses SandboxCondition\n92: - **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeStatus` struct\n93: - **WHEN** inspecting the `Conditions` field\n94: - **THEN** it SHALL be of type `[]SandboxCondition` instead of `[]AgentRuntimeCondition`\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter uses SandboxCondition\n97: - **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterStatus` struct\n98: - **WHEN** inspecting the `Conditions` field\n99: - **THEN** it SHALL be of type `[]SandboxCondition` instead of `[]CodeInterpreterCondition`\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ### Requirement: Shared Protocol Type Definition\n104: \n105: The system SHALL retain the existing `ProtocolType` definition in the shared types file for use by resources that need protocol specifications.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: ProtocolType is preserved\n108: - **GIVEN** the shared types file\n109: - **WHEN** inspecting the type definitions\n110: - **THEN** it SHALL contain a `ProtocolType` string type with kubebuilder validation enum: `HTTP`, `HTTPS`\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: ProtocolType constants are preserved\n113: - **GIVEN** the shared types file\n114: - **WHEN** inspecting the constants\n115: - **THEN** it SHALL define `ProtocolHTTP` and `ProtocolHTTPS` constants\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: TargetPort uses ProtocolType\n118: - **GIVEN** the `TargetPort` struct in `codeinterpreter_types.go`\n119: - **WHEN** inspecting the `Protocol` field\n120: - **THEN** it SHALL continue to use `ProtocolType`\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ### Requirement: Shared AuthMode Type Definition\n125: \n126: The system SHALL retain the existing `AuthModeType` definition in the shared types file for authentication mode specifications.\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: AuthModeType is preserved\n129: - **GIVEN** the shared types file\n130: - **WHEN** inspecting the type definitions\n131: - **THEN** it SHALL contain an `AuthModeType` string type with kubebuilder validation enum: `picod`, `none`\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: AuthModeType constants are preserved\n134: - **GIVEN** the shared types file\n135: - **WHEN** inspecting the constants\n136: - **THEN** it SHALL define `AuthModePicoD` and `AuthModeNone` constants\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: ### Requirement: Shared TargetPort Struct Definition\n141: \n142: The system SHALL retain the existing `TargetPort` struct definition for port configuration.\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: TargetPort struct is preserved\n145: - **GIVEN** the shared types file\n146: - **WHEN** inspecting the struct definitions\n147: - **THEN** it SHALL contain a `TargetPort` struct with the following fields:\n148:   - `PathPrefix` (string, optional)\n149:   - `Name` (string, optional)\n150:   - `Port` (uint32, required, minimum 1, maximum 65535)\n151:   - `Protocol` (`ProtocolType`, optional, default \"HTTP\")\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ### Requirement: Legacy Type Aliases for Backward Compatibility\n156: \n157: The system SHALL provide type aliases in individual CRD type files to maintain backward compatibility during the transition period.\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimePhase is aliased\n160: - **GIVEN** the `agentruntime_types.go` file\n161: - **WHEN** inspecting the type definitions after refactoring\n162: - **THEN** it SHALL contain a type alias: `type AgentRuntimePhase = SandboxPhase`\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeConditionType is aliased\n165: - **GIVEN** the `agentruntime_types.go` file\n166: - **WHEN** inspecting the type definitions after refactoring\n167: - **THEN** it SHALL contain a type alias: `type AgentRuntimeConditionType = SandboxConditionType`\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeCondition is aliased\n170: - **GIVEN** the `agentruntime_types.go` file\n171: - **WHEN** inspecting the type definitions after refactoring\n172: - **THEN** it SHALL contain a type alias: `type AgentRuntimeCondition = SandboxCondition`\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Legacy constants are aliased\n175: - **GIVEN** the `agentruntime_types.go` file\n176: - **WHEN** inspecting the constants after refactoring\n177: - **THEN** it SHALL contain constant aliases for backward compatibility (e.g., `const AgentRuntimePhasePending = SandboxPhasePending`)\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter uses shared types directly\n180: - **GIVEN** the `codeinterpreter_types.go` file\n181: - **WHEN** inspecting the type usage\n182: - **THEN** it SHALL use shared types directly without duplication (no need for aliases since CodeInterpreter was already aligned with shared patterns)\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ### Requirement: Package Structure\n187: \n188: The system SHALL organize shared types in a dedicated file within the API package.\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Types file exists\n191: - **GIVEN** the package `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n192: - **WHEN** listing files\n193: - **THEN** it SHALL contain a `types.go` file for shared type definitions\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Types file has package documentation\n196: - **GIVEN** the `types.go` file\n197: - **WHEN** inspecting the file header\n198: - **THEN** it SHALL contain appropriate package documentation comments explaining the shared types purpose\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Original files import shared types\n201: - **GIVEN** the `agentruntime_types.go` and `codeinterpreter_types.go` files\n202: - **WHEN** inspecting the imports\n203: - **THEN** no additional imports SHALL be needed since shared types are in the same package\n204: \n205: ---\n206: \n207: ### Requirement: DeepCopy Generation\n208: \n209: The system SHALL ensure DeepCopy methods are generated correctly for all shared types.\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Shared types have DeepCopy methods\n212: - **GIVEN** the generated `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` file\n213: - **WHEN** inspecting the generated code\n214: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `DeepCopyInto`, `DeepCopy`, and `DeepCopyObject` methods for `SandboxCondition`\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: Legacy types reuse shared DeepCopy\n217: - **GIVEN** the generated `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` file\n218: - **WHEN** inspecting the generated code for legacy types\n219: - **THEN** type aliases SHALL reuse the DeepCopy methods from their underlying shared types\n220: \n221: ---\n222: \n223: ### Requirement: Code Compilation\n224: \n225: The system SHALL compile successfully after the refactoring.\n226: \n227: #### Scenario: Package compiles after refactoring\n228: - **GIVEN** a clean Go module at repository root\n229: - **WHEN** the operator runs `go build ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...`\n230: - **THEN** the package SHALL compile without errors\n231: \n232: #### Scenario: Tests pass after refactoring\n233: - **GIVEN** the existing test files in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n234: - **WHEN** the operator runs `go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...`\n235: - **THEN** all tests SHALL pass\n236: \n237: ---\n238: \n239: ## File Index\n240: \n241: | Path | Purpose |\n242: |------|---------|\n243: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` | NEW: Shared type definitions (SandboxPhase, SandboxConditionType, SandboxCondition, ProtocolType, AuthModeType, TargetPort) |\n244: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go` | MODIFIED: Use shared types, add type aliases for backward compatibility |\n245: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` | MODIFIED: Remove duplicate type definitions, use shared types |\n246: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | GENERATED: Updated DeepCopy methods for shared types |\n247: \n248: ---\n249: \n250: ## Dependencies\n251: \n252: - `k8s.io/api/core/v1` — Kubernetes core types (ConditionStatus)\n253: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` — Kubernetes metadata types (Time)\n254: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` — Runtime.Object interface (implicit via type usage)\n255: \n256: ---\n257: \n258: ## Notes\n259: \n260: - Type aliases (`type X = Y`) provide compile-time equivalence, allowing existing code to continue working without modification\n261: - Shared types follow the \"Sandbox\" naming convention to indicate they apply to sandbox-based resources\n262: - The refactoring reduces code duplication while maintaining full backward compatibility\n263: - Future CRDs for sandbox-based resources can reuse these shared types\n264: - All kubebuilder markers (validation, default values) SHALL be preserved on the shared type definitions\n\n(End of file - total 264 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-003 — CRD Shared Types and Constants\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-003  \n**Module:** pkg/apis  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n\nExtract shared types and constants from AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRD definitions to reduce code duplication and establish a common type foundation for the runtime API group.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Shared Phase Type Definition\n\nThe system SHALL define a common `SandboxPhase` type to represent the lifecycle phase of sandbox-based resources, replacing the individual phase types in AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter.\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxPhase type is defined","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775844073069,"end":1775844073090}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844073095,"sessionID":"ses_287725b68ffe31vjrcaNWO7QzD","part":{"id":"prt_d788e15ae001Pn99lMk2CWODX5","messageID":"msg_d788df9bc0014YvW9GRmScDGMj","sessionID":"ses_287725b68ffe31vjrcaNWO7QzD","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/deployment/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/deployment/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Deploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Helm chart installation\n9: The system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n13: - **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n14: - **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\n17: The system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n20: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values\n21: - **WHEN** pods for `workloadmanager` and `agentcube-router` start\n22: - **THEN** each container SHALL have environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` populated from those values\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Workload Manager deployment shape\n25: The system SHALL deploy Workload Manager as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `workloadmanager` with replica count, container image, service type/port, resource requests/limits, health probes, and optional `extraEnv` driven from `values.yaml`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Default replica and service exposure\n28: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n29: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n30: - **THEN** the Workload Manager `Deployment` SHALL use `workloadmanager.replicas` (default 1), expose HTTP on `workloadmanager.service.port` (default 8080), and use liveness/readiness HTTP GET `/health` on that port\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Router deployment shape\n33: The system SHALL deploy the Router as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `agentcube-router` with replica count, image, `ClusterIP` service mapping `port`→`targetPort`, resource requests/limits, optional dedicated `serviceAccountName`, and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` pointing at the in-cluster Workload Manager service.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Router reaches Workload Manager by DNS\n36: - **GIVEN** release namespace `N` and Workload Manager service port `P` from values\n37: - **WHEN** the Router pod starts\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL have `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` set to `http://workloadmanager.N.svc.cluster.local:P` and container args including `--port=<targetPort>` and `--debug`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Workload Manager ClusterRole permissions\n41: The system SHALL create a `ServiceAccount` `workloadmanager`, a `ClusterRole` `workloadmanager`, and `ClusterRoleBinding` `workloadmanager` granting the rules required for agent-sandbox, AgentCube runtime CRDs, core workloads, auth, and secrets.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Binding ties SA to cluster role\n44: - **GIVEN** chart installation in namespace `N`\n45: - **WHEN** RBAC resources are applied\n46: - **THEN** subject `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in namespace `N` SHALL be bound to `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` via `ClusterRoleBinding/workloadmanager`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Optional Router namespace Role\n49: The system SHALL optionally create namespace-scoped `ServiceAccount`, `Role`, and `RoleBinding` for the Router when `router.rbac.create` is true, granting secret management in that namespace.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: RBAC off by default\n52: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: false`\n53: - **WHEN** the chart renders templates\n54: - **THEN** Router optional RBAC manifests SHALL NOT be emitted\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: RBAC on with named service account\n57: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: true` and `router.serviceAccountName` set (or defaulted by template to `agentcube-router`)\n58: - **WHEN** the chart is applied\n59: - **THEN** Router pods MAY use that `serviceAccountName` and the Role SHALL allow verbs on `secrets` in the release namespace\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: Optional Volcano agent scheduler\n62: The system SHALL optionally deploy Volcano agent scheduler resources (ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment) when `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is true.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Scheduler disabled\n65: - **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (default)\n66: - **WHEN** templates render\n67: - **THEN** no Volcano scheduler objects SHALL be created\n68: \n69: ### Requirement: CRDs shipped with the chart\n70: The system SHALL ship `CustomResourceDefinition` manifests for `agentruntimes` and `codeinterpreters` under the chart `crds/` directory so Helm installs them with the chart lifecycle.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: CRD group and scope\n73: - **GIVEN** chart path `manifests/charts/base`\n74: - **WHEN** CRD YAML is applied\n75: - **THEN** both CRDs SHALL use API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, and `scope: Namespaced`\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Docker images for core binaries\n78: The system SHALL provide Dockerfiles to build three images: Workload Manager (`docker/Dockerfile`), Router (`docker/Dockerfile.router`), and picod (`docker/Dockerfile.picod`).\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Multi-stage Go build for control plane\n81: - **GIVEN** repository root as build context\n82: - **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile` (or `Dockerfile.router`) runs\n83: - **THEN** the image SHALL compile the respective Go binary with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and run it from Alpine 3.19 as a non-root user (`apiserver` UID 1000 or `router` UID 1000) exposing port 8080\n84: \n85: ### Requirement: Makefile build targets\n86: The system SHALL expose Make targets to build binaries (`build`, related targets), run tests (`test`), build/push Docker images (`docker-*`), run code generation (`generate`, `gen-crd`, `gen-client`, `gen-all`, `gen-check`), and run E2E (`e2e`, `e2e-clean`).\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Default `make` builds workload manager\n89: - **GIVEN** Go toolchain and generated code prerequisites\n90: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make` (default `all` → `build`)\n91: - **THEN** `bin/workloadmanager` SHALL be produced from `./cmd/workload-manager` after `generate`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: E2E entrypoint\n94: - **GIVEN** Kind, kubectl, Docker, Helm, and curl available\n95: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make e2e`\n96: - **THEN** the repository SHALL execute `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` which provisions the cluster (unless skipped), deploys dependencies, and runs Go and Python E2E tests\n\n(End of file - total 96 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Specification\n\n## Purpose\nDeploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Helm chart installation\nThe system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n\n#### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n- **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n- **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n\n### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\nThe system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n\n#### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n- **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/deployment/spec.md","time":{"start":1775844073071,"end":1775844073093}}}}
