{"type":"text","timestamp":1775844390117,"sessionID":"ses_287725b68ffe31vjrcaNWO7QzD","part":{"id":"prt_d7892d825001EdiebEYJ1PPuaN","messageID":"msg_d78929fd2001WLXHYaeSsTz0GL","sessionID":"ses_287725b68ffe31vjrcaNWO7QzD","type":"text","text":"I've written the delta-spec.md for **AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework**. The spec includes 14 major requirements with detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios:\n\n1. **HTTP Server Bootstrap** - Server lifecycle, graceful shutdown, TLS\n2. **Health and Readiness Endpoints** - `/healthz`, `/readyz` with dependency checks\n3. **RESTful API for AgentRuntime Resources** - CRUD + Watch operations\n4. **RESTful API for CodeInterpreter Resources** - CRUD + Watch operations  \n5. **Resource Status Endpoints** - Status subresource management\n6. **Kubernetes Client Integration** - In-cluster/kubeconfig, typed clientset\n7. **Request Routing and Middleware** - Logging, recovery, CORS, auth\n8. **Request/Response Serialization** - JSON handling, error formats\n9. **Query Parameter Support** - Label/field selectors, pagination\n10. **Metrics and Observability** - Prometheus metrics\n11. **Structured Logging** - Configurable log levels, field-based logging\n12. **Configuration Management** - Environment variables, validation\n13. **Error Handling** - Kubernetes API error mapping\n14. **Server Command Line Interface** - CLI entry point with flags\n\nThe spec is written in OpenSpec format at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md`.","time":{"start":1775844390114,"end":1775844390114}}}
